Summary (Simple)
1️⃣ Resource Quotas
A ResourceQuota is used to limit the total resources used in a project (namespace).
It restricts:
•	CPU
•	Memory
•	Storage
•	Number of objects (pods, services, etc.)
Example
requests.memory = 2Gi
limits.memory = 4Gi
Meaning:
Resource	Limit
Total memory requested	2Gi
Total memory used (limit)	4Gi
If the project exceeds these values → new pods cannot be created.
👉 Used to prevent one project from consuming the whole cluster resources.
________________________________________
2️⃣ Cluster Resource Quotas
Normal quotas apply per project.
But sometimes admins want quotas across multiple projects.
That is where ClusterResourceQuota is used.
It works using labels.
Example
team=dev
All projects with label team=dev share the same quota.
________________________________________
3️⃣ Limit Ranges
LimitRange controls resources per container or pod inside a project.
It defines:
Setting	Meaning
Default	Applied if user does not specify limits
DefaultRequest	Default resource request
Min	Minimum allowed resource
Max	Maximum allowed resource
Example
defaultRequest: 256Mi
default: 512Mi
min: 128Mi
max: 1Gi
Meaning:
Rule	Value
Minimum memory	128Mi
Default request	256Mi
Default limit	512Mi
Maximum memory	1Gi
So if a developer creates a pod without specifying memory, OpenShift automatically assigns:
Request = 256Mi
Limit = 512Mi
________________________________________
4️⃣ Project Template
Admins can create a custom project template so every new project automatically gets:
•	ResourceQuota
•	LimitRange
•	RoleBindings
•	Other resources
Workflow
User creates project
        ↓
OpenShift uses template
        ↓
Quota + LimitRange + Roles automatically created
Example:
oc new-project myapp
Automatically creates:
ResourceQuota
LimitRange
RoleBinding
________________________________________
5️⃣ Self-Provisioner Role
The self-provisioner role controls who can create projects.
Default behavior:
All authenticated users can create projects
Because they are bound to:
ClusterRole: self-provisioner
Admins can restrict it.
Example
Remove project creation access:
oc adm policy remove-cluster-role-from-group \
self-provisioner system:authenticated
Then only specific users/groups can create projects.
________________________________________
🔑 Complete Flow (Important for Exam)
Cluster Admin
      │
      ├── ResourceQuota → limits total resources in project
      │
      ├── LimitRange → limits resources per container
      │
      ├── Project Template → standard configuration for new projects
      │
      └── Self-Provisioner → controls who can create projects
________________________________________
🚀 Real Example (From Your Lab)
Project template creates automatically:
LimitRange
  defaultRequest: 256Mi
  default: 512Mi
  min: 128Mi
  max: 1Gi

ResourceQuota
  requests.memory: 2Gi
  limits.memory: 4Gi
So:
1 pod → request 256Mi
8 pods → request 2Gi
Quota reached → 9th pod cannot start.
________________________________________
✅ Key idea
Component	Controls
ResourceQuota	Total resources per project
LimitRange	Resource limits per container
Project Template	Default project configuration
Self-Provisioner	Who can create projects

